00:32:42,014 --> 00:32:44,795
despite having a thousand elixirs,

627
00:32:44,795 --> 00:32:46,516
feeling compelled to collect everything

628
00:32:46,516 --> 00:32:50,398
even if it means hours of not having fun,

629
00:32:50,398 --> 00:32:51,958
and of course, speed running.

630
00:32:51,958 --> 00:32:53,659
It's just, just kidding.

631
00:32:53,659 --> 00:32:57,701
Um, moving on, I believe that the term min-maxing

632
00:32:57,701 --> 00:33:00,502
originally came from D&D and RPGs

633
00:33:00,502 --> 00:33:03,063
when you would use math to perfectly optimize a character

634
00:33:03,063 --> 00:33:04,864
for a very specific purpose.

635
00:33:04,864 --> 00:33:06,625
However, I'm using the term to describe

636
00:33:06,625 --> 00:33:07,685
something slightly different.

637
00:33:08,554 --> 00:33:11,155
In short, the compulsion to do the most optimal play,

638
00:33:11,155 --> 00:33:13,335
even to the detriment of my own enjoyment of the game.

639
00:33:13,335 --> 00:33:17,316
The feeling that forces me to Google best leveling priest

640
00:33:17,316 --> 00:33:20,557
build in Ragnarok Online, the feeling that I simply

641
00:33:20,557 --> 00:33:22,477
have to grind each unit to level 20

642
00:33:22,477 --> 00:33:25,158
before I advance classes in Fire Emblem,

643
00:33:25,158 --> 00:33:28,879
needing to get plus fives in every single level in Oblivion.

644
00:33:28,879 --> 00:33:31,039
My problem isn't that you can game the system

645
00:33:31,039 --> 00:33:32,960
by being as efficient as possible.

646
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:35,160
My problem is when it's specifically not fun to do so.

647
00:33:36,740 --> 00:33:40,821
That being said, this compulsion is not always problematic.

648
00:33:40,821 --> 00:33:42,581
In MMOs, it's critical to optimize

649
00:33:42,581 --> 00:33:44,862
your combat efficiency for raids.

